description:
While strange attacks wreak havoc across the country, the Freedom Fighters are trapped in a maximum security prison courtesy of the menacing King Bullet! Who will fight for their freedom now?
 
The Freedom Fighters have no idea that Enclave A (the Grindhouse) even existed until they were neck deep in a prison riot.  At first the Freedom Fighters try to reason with the prisoners.  This leads you Firebrand getting severely wounded and the whole team tossed down into a pit of failed experiments with collars that inhibit their powers.  Meanwhile King Bullet is setting opon his dream of Freedom but the Warden has set a twenty minute self destruct in the facility and all of a sudden King Bullet needs the Freedom Fighters, or at least Phantom Lady to get out before they are all dead.
 
At the end of the comic there is a six page preview for the DC Universe Legends online #1 comic book.
name: American Nightmare Part Five!

description:
The explosive ACTION COMICS / SECRET SIX crossover concludes here! At the paid request of Lex Luthor, the Secret Six rush headlong into a deadly confrontation with Scandal's villainous father, Vandal Savage. But the Six have a score of their own to settle with Luthor, and unlike Superman, the Six fight dirty. Don't miss this grudge match finale between DC's smartest villain and DC's weirdest team!   
*Continued from Action Comics #896
name: What Luthor Has Wrought

description:
The Inhumans lead the Kree Empire against the forces of Vulcan and the Shi’ar – and Black Bolt has a battle plan that will transform the entire universe!

Also: The Wasp wants his greatest invention back from Mr Fantastic – but why is he refusing to return it?! The Mighty Avengers clash with the Fantastic Four!

Includes material reprinted from War of Kings #4-5 and Mighty Avengers #25.

The Doom Patrol just met The Aristocrats, and how better to follow a punchline than with some actual punching? The world's strangest Super Heroes face off with the world's most horrific family – and they've never had a fight like this before!
name: Gut Instinct

description: How do you survive a zombie apocalypse? Believe us when we tell you, it is far from easy. Find out how our heroes escaped the aftermath of Raise the Dead Vol. 1 and get a peek at the horrors they had to endure in order to reach Alfredo Bay. With more gore and zombies than you can shake a shotgun at, this issue is guaranteed to knock you off your feet… or at least make you a little bit queasy.
A strange series of events in the spree killer case drives a wedge between Detective Curt Delatte and the only thing he's ever been good at - his job...
name: 4 of 5

description:
In the midst of the darkest days of World War II, Sector Seven's greatest fear has come true-the Nazis have captured a TRANSFORMER!

The group's seven deadliest soldiers-a rag-tag group of screw-ups and cast-offs in any other context-go on what's surely a suicide mission into the heart of Nazi Germany!
name: Weapon

description:
The most dangerous Decepticon in the universe is back... but not in a way anyone expected. What has happened to Megatron in his years away, and what is his plan for his enemies? Costa and Figueroa reveal all, as the darkest chapter since ALL HAIL MEGATRON continues!

With bumblebee getting shot by an ordinary human, tension begins to mount on the transformers as sides are being picked among the nations of the world. human fanaticals taking up arms in paranoia of an impending alien attack from the transformers and the long awaited return of megatron. and the plan that is set in motion to undo the autobots on earth as they exact their revenge in: Revenge of the Decepticons!
name: Revenge of the Decepticons Part 2: Altered Carbon

description:
The final battle with the Marquis of Death has arrived – but Reed Richards’s only hope of defeating him lies in the murder of an innocent man! Tragedy strikes the FF in an all-action epic!

Also: classic 1960s adventure! The FF invade the mysterious Beehive to save Alicia Masters!

Collects:

Fantastic Four (1961) #66

Fantastic Four (1961) #67

Fantastic Four (1961) #569
name: The Marquis of Death!

description: A gladiator wanted for having an affair with a noble is hunted by a bounty hunter in the desert. Upon his "capture" the gladiator and the bounty hunter are attacked by desert creatures and  they make a plan to find the fabled Under-Tyr and treasure that is contained within using the gladiators medallion.
name: 1 (of 5)

name: Mr. Gum

description: 3 issue mini-series published by Image Comics and featuring Savage Dragon.
name: Part 1

description:
Green Hornet and Kato's battle with the deadly Santa Muerte gang takes a turn for the bizarre when the Saint of Death itself takes a hand.
When Britt is captured by police, a detective discovers the truth about Green Hornet's cover as a crime lord, leaving Mulan alone to face the maniacal cult.

Plus, the original Kato and Clutch are caught in the coils of the remnants of the Juuma clan in Japan.
name: Idols, Part Two: Unmasked

name: Madman Adventures

name: Spaceman

description:
The Next Men are lost in time: Nathan falls in the middle of a WW II battle, Jasmine was taken away in the British Renaissance and Tony Murcheson ends up in the American Civil War, a difficult era for an afro-american woman. 
As to Jack, he seems to had became a Catholic Father in a short future.
name: Scattered, Part 2

description: The Doc must come up with a way to capture the evil ghost that is haunting his clients, with the help of Lloyd his trusty robot companion, he uses his scientific genius to discover a way to trap the dead.
